author: Jacob Kagi
title: Two more WA deaths from COVID-19, including man from Artania cruise ship
description: Western Australia has recorded two more COVID-19 deaths, with a patient from the Artania cruise ship and a West Australian woman aged in her 70s dying in hospital.
content:
Updated 
April 07, 2020 17:28:48
Western Australia has recorded two more COVID-19 deaths, bringing the toll of the virus in the state to six.
An overseas man aged in his 70s who was infected on the Artania cruise ship has died at Joondalup Hospital.
